State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ranging in sizes from slightly larger than an ordinary Daedroth to sizes that are only surpassed by a Daedric Titan or similar abomination, these Daedroth Titans with far superior physical power and magical potency were rewarded with their new mighty forms for their effectiveness and loyalty in service to their Daedric Princes.
State.Name: Daedroth Titans- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''oblivion daedra'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Dryads are forest nymphs, protectors of flowers and trees, guardians of the ancient woodlands and everything that germinates in their sacred soil. Unlike Spriggans, Dryads appear to be specifically connected to flora, while Spriggans have an equally deep connection to animals as they do to plants.
State.Name: Dryads - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''spriggan'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ornaugs are marine reptiles with a canine appearance and amphibious life, native to the warm waters of the Abecean Sea and used as mounts by the Maormer. Plates of reinforced scales cover some parts of their body, especially those that cover the entire head, giving them a hard, bony-looking helmet.
State.Name: Amenos Ornaugs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''eso'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The elemental power of fire, ice and shock personified in these mighty golems, the ideal conjurations for any powerful wizard and now all in one bundle for you.
State.Name: Elemental Golems- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Honi was the faithful cat companion of the now deceased conjurer Rhorald, and his most beloved friend. When he died, his owner conjured a magical body of ice for him, where he placed his soul, so that Honi would remain by his side forever. Now Honi is looking for a new friend to follow on magical adventures across Tamriel.
State.Name: Honi the Frost Atronach Cat- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: These brutal creatures of fearsome strength, but low intelligence and foul smell, now all in one single file. Prepare your shield and your nose!
State.Name: Ogres and Ettins- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

Original.Name: Old Gods of the Hunt (SE) 1.4.1 version-27520-1-4-1-1651832785.rar

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Old Gods of the Hunt are powerfull and mysterious ancient creatures from a previous Wild Hunt, that still roams through Tamriel in very small numbers in the current era. Ferocious and stunning powerfull, this Wild Hunt beasts are connected to Hircine, and worshiped since the beginning by the Reachmen and the Bosmer as one of their Old Gods.
State.Name: Old Gods of the Hunt- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''the witcher'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Both of these gigantic races that inspired some of the most terrifying sailor stories are now compiled in one mod. The shores of Skyrim will become a dangerous place to cross, even for the bravest pirate.
State.Name: Sea Giants and Ice Titans- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Trolls native to Cyrodiil are smaller, less dangerous, and curiously more covered in thick fur than their northern counterparts. However, the temperament is the same, and their smell is nauseating, with the thick fur arranged in a tangle of parasites, food scraps, dirt and even moss.
State.Name: Trolls of Cyrodiil - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Wraith of Crows is a fearsome winged creature, resembling a skeletal humanoid crow with large black feathered wings and torn clothing, and magically formed by combining the power of several Crow Daedra, the sentient corvidians of Evergloam, the realm of Nocturnal. Of considerable magical power, they also resort to a one-handed scythe in combat.
State.Name: Wraith-of-Crows - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''nocturnal'')

State.Author: JaySerpa

State.Name: Civil War Lines Expansion

State.Author: AdamDunmer
State.Description: Hello! Thanks for navigating to this page you lovely, beautiful person! This mod is the first part of a series of dialogue expansions for several projects I have planned. This adds over 100 lines of voiced dialogue to MannyGt's fantastic "Books of Skyrim" mod. It's all voiced with Elevenlabs AI. ESL-flagged esp. Demonstration in "video" tab.
State.Name: Dialogue Expansion-Books of Skyrim.

State.Author: AdamDunmer
State.Description: Hello! This mod adds 150+ lore-friendly lines of dialogue to Imperial soldiers across Skyrim! There is a plenitude of new "Greet" lines as well as thirteen new scenes (NPC-NPC conversations). They also have new things to chat about depending on the player's progress in the Civil War Imperial questline. ESPFE. Voiced by Elevenlabs AI.
State.Name: Dialogue Expansion - Imperial Soldiers

State.Author: AdamDunmer
State.Description: Hello! This is the second part of a series of several planned dialogue expansions to liven the world of Skyrim. This mod adds around 150 lines of dialogue (149 to be exact) to various Khajiiti caravan merchants around Skyrim. Also, 3 scenes have been added between Ri'saad and Ma'randru Jo. ESPFE. Voiced via Elevenlabs AI. Updates to come!
State.Name: Dialogue Expansion- Khajiit Caravans

State.Author: AdamDunmer
State.Description: Hello! This is yet another dialogue expansion to liven the world of Skyrim. This mod adds around 140 lines of dialogue (137 in total) to the NPCS in the title. Four scenes (NPC conversations) have been added as well (2 for Indaryn, 1 each for Ingun/Asgeir). Voiced via Elevenlabs AI. ESPFE, so it won't take up a spot in your load order.
State.Name: Dialogue Expansion- Indaryn-Ingun-Asgeir-Alessandra

State.Author: AdamDunmer
State.Description: Hello! This mod adds around 250 lines of dialogue to the existing denizens of Shor's Stone: Odfel, Sylgja, Grogmar, and Filnjar. The player has more to talk about(Ask Sylgja about how her family's doing, etc). I also added 9 more scenes (NPC-NPC convos) between them all. So, sit down by the campfire and enjoy the dialogue! Voiced by 11labs AI.ESPFE
State.Name: Dialogue Expansion- Shor's Stone

State.Author: AdamDunmer
State.Description: Hello! This mod adds 1350+ lore-friendly lines of dialogue to the existing residents of Windhelm (about 30 NPCS are modified). NPCS were given major dialogue overhauls so as to really represent the sterile, hostile nature of Windhelm, itself. I also added around 30 more scenes (NPC-NPC conversations) between them all. Voiced by 11labs AI. ESPFE
State.Name: Dialogue Expansion - Windhelm

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The Ancient Nordic Sentinels are a type of gigantic Foundation Stone Golem made of old norse architecture. Guardians of the ancient tombs, and the terror of their invaders, these fearsome colossi animated by the souls of powerful warriors will crush all foes with no mercy.
State.Name: Ancient Nordic Sentinel- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''golem'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: All Mihail's chicken and chick mods compiled in one esp. Replace the ugly vanilla chickens and even add new color varieties, plus adorable chicks following them around.
State.Name: Chickens and Chicks- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Bundle of Mihail's Draugr Cavalry and Draugr Patrols mods in one esp. The terrifying nordic undead will haunt your nightmares every night from now on after you install this mod.
State.Name: Draugr Patrols and Cavalry- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Small, harmless frog critters hopping around in the lakes and puddles of Skyrim, giving your world an extra touch of life and immersion.
State.Name: Frogs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Compilation of Mihail's Classic Ghosts and Mourning Souls mods in one esp. Take Skyrim's spooky haunts to the next level with this terrifying add-on.
State.Name: Ghosts and Souls- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE) (''undead'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Complete overhaul of the vanilla Giants, diversifying the appearance of the males, and adding several variants of Giantesses and also a juvenile version. It never made sense that all Giants were male and looked exactly the same, so this mod is here to solve this problem once and for all.
State.Name: Giants Overhaul- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Now compiled into a single mod, the pesky Goblins and Riekrs clans will make your exploration of the world more interesting and challenging.
State.Name: Goblins and Riekrs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: These two gargantuan daedra of unparalleled power now available in a compilation for your conjurer character. They will crush anyone foolish enough to dare confront you.
State.Name: Havocrels and Ruinachs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: High Clannfears are aggressive saurian humanoids from Oblivion, with large spike-covered bony crests adorning their heads, and with sharp beaks and long claws specially designed to tear their prey to shreds. Intelligent, but bordering on bestiality, they are often used and trained by higher Daedra as guard dogs.
State.Name: High Clannfears - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: House cats are docile little felines, often kept as pets in towns and villages. Although initially domesticated to hunt rats that destroyed food and spread diseases, the excess of pampering and treats made most city cats have chubby bodies and lazy behavior. In Skyrim, you'll encounter them in almost every city and farm.
State.Name: House Cats- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''pet'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Both traditional small winged pesky critters in a single file. They will add an extra touch of mischievousness to your world exploration.
State.Name: Imps and Homonculus- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Compilation of all of Mihail's Minotaur mods in one esp. The forests will never be the same, now patrolled by these fierce bull-men, descendants of the demigod Morihaus
State.Name: Minotaurs - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''oblivion'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Previously restricted to being just a single, forgettable encounter from the Dawnguard DLC, these ancient versions of the Frost Atronach can now be found in more locations, and are also summonable. Additionally, they now have higher quality textures and more unique battle effects.
State.Name: More Ancient Frost Atronachs- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: These dangerous and solitary predatory felines are fast, agile and, like all cats, devilishly cunning. Whether in surprise ambush attacks or head-to-head confrontations, the sharp claws and powerful jaws of one of these panthers is always a force to be reckoned with.
State.Name: Mountain Lions and Panthers- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Ogrims are a type of ogre-like enormous daedra with very little intellect and enormous raw power. They are sent into the mortal world to menace living things for the amusement of the Daedric Princes, and are mostly associated with Malacath. Many scholars even speculate them to be a daedric corruption of the Ogres made by Malacath himself.
State.Name: Ogrim- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''daedra'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The brave and proud guardians of the chicken coops. Generally only one is maintained per farm, as they are territorial and clashes can end in bloody, often fatal fights.
State.Name: Roosters- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''chicken'')

State.Author: Sergg Mihail
State.Description:
The mod changes the proportions of the rooster's body.

If you liked please come back and Endorse. Thank you!
State.Name: Mihail's Rooster Proportions

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Peaceful and cute Sea Turtle critters swimming majestically through the oceans around Skyrim, while avidly devouring fields of kelp, giving your world an extra touch of life and beauty.
State.Name: Sea Turtles- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: This large feline is a relentless predator, even managing to take down Mammoths of considerable size when hunting in groups. Although the term is also used to define all members of the most well-known and abundant feline family of saber-toothed predators, it is the largest among these that is usually individually referred to as Smilodon.
State.Name: Smilodon- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''megafauna'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Sprites are timid nature spirits resembling small floating orbs, usually blue in color, with two pairs of transparent wings. They produce a sparkling, magical sound and pose no danger. Several stories tell of heroes who were guided by Sprites during their journeys until they reached their goals.
State.Name: Sprites- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''fairy'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: Encounters with Zombies and Wights, while always unpleasant, are relatively common for an adventurer exploring Skyrim, but tales of an encounter with a reanimated ancient Snow Elf is something that strays into the realm of myth, and will make many roll their eyes, as if they were listening to just another fairy tale, told to frighten children.
State.Name: Undead Snow Elves- Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version) (''falmer'')

State.Author: Mihail
State.Description: The wolves that inhabit Cyrodiil are smaller than their nordic cousins, however, these pack predators prove to be just as efficient as their larger relatives. They can be found in Skyrim mainly near the border with their home province, with some packs migrating to regions further north.
State.Name: Wolves of Cyrodiil - Mihail Monsters and Animals (SE-AE version)
